# Code quality

## File length

- Target ≤150 lines, aim to stay well under ~200 per file
- When a file grows, split by responsibility:
  - Fat screen → extract child components into a `components/` folder
  - Fat store → split selectors/actions into focused modules
  - Fat service (backend) → `service/create.py`, `service/search.py`, etc.
- Never hit the target by deleting error handling, types, or needed docs - split instead

## No legacy / dead code

This is a fresh assessment project - do not keep backwards-compat shims.

- No routes/exports named `legacy`, `old`, `deprecated`
- When replacing something, migrate all callers and delete the old path - no stubs
- No parallel fields/DTOs for the same concept
- No commented-out blocks left behind

## Clean diffs

- Match existing patterns and naming; don't refactor unrelated code
- Keep changes minimal and focused on the request
- No `console.log` in committed code - use `console.warn` / `console.error` only when needed

## Before finishing

- `pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck` clean on touched packages
- No new lint warnings introduced
